  "doc_id": "5860",
  "text": "The four species showed some walking activity at 8°C, below the threshold for flying. Walking is an important part of intra-patch searching behaviour and the fact that walking was observed at low temperature indicates that parasitism remains possible at this temperature if females are already in the vicinity of an aphid colony. In our case, all individuals moved with little difference in speed contrary to [CITATION_1] who observed an important interindividual variability of walking activities of Trichogramma brassicae at 12°C probably linked to the fact that the activity threshold of this species is close to that temperature.",
